text.content: I rolled my cart out of my apartment and locked my front door . I dragged the empty cart down the stairs and pushed it down the block toward the supermarket . As I walked , I mentally rehearsed some of the items I intended to buy . I needed eggs , milk , bread , cookies , and bananas . Maybe I would get a few other things if they looked good . I arrived at the store and hooked my cart to the store 's larger metal shopping cart . I pushed it down the aisle . I passed the section with the bread fist , and put it in my cart . The cookies were near the bread . I took a while looking at the ingredients for different packages of cookies and finally decided to get a box that looked fresh and delicious without too many preservatives . I put my chosen cookies into my cart and kept pushing . I reached the refrigerated section and found the milk . I added a carton to my cart , and also chose some yogurt . I looked at the eggs and checked them for cracks before adding them . Then I turned my cart toward the fruit and vegetable aisle . I added bananas and then my eye caught some avocados that were on sale , so I decided to buy two of them . I also got a few apples and a box of cherry tomatoes . I rolled my cart toward the cashier and got on line to pay . When it was my turn I paid in cash and then put my bagged items into my cart . Then I pushed my cart home and unloaded my items in my kitchen .
